{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:47:51.043627+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, both file-writing approaches return a **403 \"Resource not accessible by personal access token\"** error — this is a repository permission issue with the provided token that retrying cannot resolve.\n\nHowever, I have fully analyzed the issue and prepared the changes. Here is my complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #5 — Add endpoint allowlist documentation\n\n### What the issue requires\nDocument which local demo endpoints are intentionally in scope for the ZAP baseline workflow, updating:\n- `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` (already exists and is complete)\n- `docs/in_scope_endpoints.md` (needs to be expanded)\n\n### Current state\n- **`policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml`** — Already contains the two allowlisted endpoints (`http://127.0.0.1:8080/` and `http://localhost:8080/`). No changes needed.\n- **`docs/in_scope_endpoints.md`** — Currently just a one-liner: *\"Only local demo endpoints listed in `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` are in scope.\"* This needs to be expanded with the actual endpoint details, rationale, and scope enforcement context.\n\n### Prepared change for `docs/in_scope_endpoints.md`\n\nThe updated file would contain:\n\n```markdown\n# In-Scope Endpoints\n\nThis document lists the local demo endpoints that are intentionally in scope for the ZAP baseline workflow.\n\n## Allowlisted Endpoints\n\nThe following endpoints are defined in `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml`:\n\n| Endpoint | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `http://127.0.0.1:8080/` | Loopback address for the local demo application |\n| `http://localhost:8080/` | Localhost alias for the same demo application |\n\n## Demo Application\n\nThe demo application (`app.py`) serves a single plain-text page on port 8080. It is intended for local ZAP baseline testing only and is not exposed beyond the loopback interface.\n\n## Scope Rules\n\n- Only endpoints listed in `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` should be scanned.\n- The baseline scan helper (`scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`) enforces local-only targets and will refuse non-local addresses.\n- All endpoints resolve to the same local demo server running on `127.0.0.1:8080`.\n```\n\n### Validation\nThe `scripts/validate_repo.py` script checks for required files and the non-local target rejection guard — neither is affected by this documentation-only change, so `make validate` would continue to pass.\n\n### Limitation\nI was unable to commit the file due to a **403 permission error** on the GitHub API. The PAT token lacks write access to this repository. The changes above are ready to be applied once write access is available.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 628, "prompt_tokens": 13440, "total_tokens": 14068, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 40, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 12928, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0008156208, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002692608, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00054636}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780865259-hGH82fAUHIswXp5LQx5t", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3d7-565e-70f0-b039-e645dfb64d95-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13440, "output_tokens": 628, "total_tokens": 14068, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 12928}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 40}}}}]}}}
